Method Detail

addImportDeclaration

@Deprecated
void addImportDeclaration(java.lang.CharSequence pImportPath)
                          throws JSourceObjectizerException
Deprecated. JSourceObjectizer 2.xx feature; should be seen as experimental.

Adds a stated import declaration.

Parameters:
pImportPath - The path of the imported type. Note that the keyword import and the semicolon at the end of the import declaration will be added automatically by this method.
Throws:
JSourceObjectizerException - if parsing fails.

getAnnotationDeclarations

Returns:
A list of the annotation declarations. If there are no annotation declarations null will be returned.

getAnnotationDeclarations

java.util.List<AnnotationDeclaration> getAnnotationDeclarations(java.util.List<AnnotationDeclaration> pList)
Returns a list of the annotation declarations.

Parameters:
pList - If this argument isn't null the annotation declarations will be added to this list and this list object will be returned. Otherwise a new list will be created for the result.
Returns:
A list of the annotation declarations. If there are no annotation declarations null will be returned, even if the argument pList isn't null.
See Also:
getTypeDeclarations(List)

getAnnotations

java.util.List<Annotation> getAnnotations()
If the Java source is a package-info.java file (i.e. a file with package annotations) this method returns a list of the annotations.

Calling this method equals an getAnnotations(null) call.

Returns:
A list of package annotations. If the Java source isn't a package-info.java file null will be returned.
See Also:
getAnnotations(List), isPackageInfoSource()
